<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-07T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-07T04:00:00-05:00" n="38" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.927/105: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-07T11:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                        1926—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 7—10:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>11. Your instruction number 249, February 2nd and subsequent
                            correspondence. Am only today advised both British and French
                            representatives approve draft of note. Shall I present draft transmitted
                            by Department? Believe Egyptian Government likely to accede.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>